article.headline: Norfolk St. 74, Winston-Salem 50
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Michael Deloach scored 18 points to lead five Norfolk State players in double figures in a 74-50 victory over Winston-Salem State on Saturday. Brandon Wheeless went 4-for-4 from the field and 5-for-5 from the line to score a career-high 15 points for the Spartans (8-17), who won their third consecutive game. Norfolk State led throughout, taking a 22-9 advantage on Aleek Pauline's layup with 8:15 remaining in the first half and 37-26 on Rob Hampton's three-point play with 17:29 to play. Deloach's two free throws gave the Spartans a 58-42 lead with 6:44 to play. Kyle O'Quinn scored 13 points and Hampton and Tim Zephyr added 10 points each for Norfolk State, which shot 61.5 percent from the floor (16-for-26) in the second half. Paul Davis scored 15 points for Winston-Salem State (10-15), which lost for the third time in four games.
